class="postbody">I'd like to add my 2c here as a high level woodworker, 47 to be exact.
<br />

<br />
I think the last time I tried to make arrows around level 20 ish which my little experiment showed they were a huge pita to make, requiring 6 subcomes to make 1 arrow combine, which to be fair can make up to 20 arrows now I beleive. The cose of thse ingredient at the time was enough for me to wonder who would possibly pay that much extra for arrows when store bought are so much easier to get.  I dread to think of the costs now with the new fuel charges. 
<br />

<br />
Arrows should be the simplist thing for any woodworker to make, instead they are one of the most complicated. They should be 1 combines, or at most 2 combines, like quills and I think all the sub combines should be ones that the woodworker can make, instead of using metal workers to supply bars, even though with the new skills they can in theory make them themselves.
<br />

<br />
Player made arrows should be quick and easy to make in bulk, a cost similar to store bought, definately not more then twice the price, and perform better. Until these things happen I can't see myself making arrows for any real reason.<br />_________________<br />Faille
